title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland Auditorium Arena on 1981-12-28
lineage: Master Cassettes (Dolby B)(Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz)> dBpoweramp 2496 > Adobe Audition 3.01 > TLH flac2496
description:
Set I
Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Peggy-O-> El Paso, Loser, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed-> Beat It On Down The Line, Good Time Blues, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance
Set II
China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: NYE Run '81: N3 I agree with kbmill (in other stream), this show is sort of the oddball of the run. While not as good as the first two, it's still really good! Garcia tunes are great from the first set with an excellent set closing Lost Sailor -> Saint. Space is groovy -> O1.

50 something years ago this Stella Blue. 
that's all.
